== Rice ==

Wash and dry all produce. Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Mince @garlic{2%clove}. Zest and halve @lime{1}. Thinly slice @scallions{2}, keeping greens and whites separate. Bring 1 cup salted water to a boil in a #small pot{}. Once boiling, add @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}. Cover and simmer until tender, about ~{15%minutes}. Keep covered.

== Broccoli ==

Toss @broccoli florets{8%ounce} on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{4%teaspoon} and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast until golden brown and slightly crispy, ~{15-20%minutes}.

== Beef Skewers ==

Combine @beef sirloin tips{12%ounce}, @soy sauce{1%tablespoon}, @sugar{2%teaspoon}, half the garlic, @lime zest{1/2%tsp}, and a large drizzle of olive oil in a #medium bowl{}. Season with salt and pepper.

Preheat broiler to high (or oven to 500 degrees). Rinse @wooden skewers{4} under water, then thread steak onto them. Place on baking sheet and broil, flipping over halfway through, until slightly charred and cooked to desired doneness, about ~{5-10%minutes}.

== Peanut Dipping Sauce ==

Heat a drizzle of olive oil in a #medium pan{} over low heat. Add scallion whites and remaining garlic, and toss until fragrant, about ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir @peanut butter{2%tablespoon}, @soy sauce{1%tsp}, and @sugar{2%teaspoon} into pan. Slowly stir in 1/4 cup water until incorporated. Remove pan from heat, and stir in a squeeze of lime. Season to taste with salt and pepper.

== To Serve ==

Serve satay on a bed of rice alongside broccoli. Garnish with scallion greens, and serve with peanut sauce for dipping.

> Satay is a popular dish throughout Southeast Asia that features skewered meat and a creamy peanut sauce. It's commonly served as a snack food, but we bulked it up into a meal with the help of fragrant jasmine rice and crispy roasted broccoli.